   <abstract>Civil defense insert into the August 31, 1969, issue of the Nashville Tennessean instructing citizens how to deal with a nuclear blast. The front page gives basic information of how to protect one's self, how to take cover, and on nuclear fallout. The successive maps enumerate fall out shelters, shelter clusters, occupants only shelters, and occupants only clusters across Davidson County as well as a color-coded key.</abstract>
   <abstract>Most substantial cities across the nation issued these Community Shelter Plans to instruct citizens how to prepare for and act after a nuclear blast. Local offices of Civil Defense coordinated with state and local planning commissions to distribute these maps and informational booklets to citizens.</abstract>
